com.bham.bd.audio

Class AudioAutomatedTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bham.bd.audio.AudioAutomatedTest

  • public class AudioAutomatedTest
extends Object

    Automated audio tests

    This class runs a couple of JUnits tests to check some instantiation of players and the volume parameters.

    • shouldCreateAudioClipFromEveryEffect() - ensures an audio object for every SoundEffect can be created properly
    • shouldCreateMediaFromEveryTrack() - ensures an audio object for every SoundTrack can be created properly
    • shouldHaveNoEffectOnNullPlayer() - ensures no UI method call (e.g., play(), pause()) has effect on non-loaded AudioManager
    • shouldNotCreateEmptySequentialPlayer(SoundTrack[]) - ensures SequentialAudioPlayer is not created on empty array of sound tracks
    • shouldNotCreateEmptySequentialPlayer(SoundTrack[][]) - ensures SequentialAudioPlayer is not created on empty array of arrays of sound tracks
    • shouldNotCreateEmptySequentialPlayer(SoundTrack[]) - ensures ParallelAudioPlayer is not created on empty array of sound tracks
    • volumeUpperBound() - ensures anything above 1 is set back to 1 for audio volume
    • volumeLowerBound() - ensures anything below 0 is set back to 0 for audio volume

      • oneDimensionalEmptyPlayer

        private Object[] oneDimensionalEmptyPlayer()
        Provides an array of parameters to test 1D creation of an empty player

        Note: we don't test for potential null values a sound track array might have:

        • new SoundTrack[]{ null }
        • new SoundTrack[]{ null, null }

        This is because such errors are caught and we already did a test ensuring no value for any SoundTrack converted to Media is null.

        Returns:
        array of possible values which should not load the player

      • twoDimensionalEmptyPlayer

        private Object[] twoDimensionalEmptyPlayer()
        Provides an array of parameters to test 2D creation of an empty player

        Note: we don't test for potential null values a sound track array might have:

        • new SoundTrack[][]{ new SoundTrack[]{ null } }
        • new SoundTrack[][]{ new SoundTrack[]{ null, null }, new SoundTrack[]{} }

        This is because such errors are caught and we already did a test ensuring no value for any SoundTrack converted to Media is null.

        Returns:
        array of possible values which should not load the player
